               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib306-1">Textes dans Bedjan, Jab-Alaha, 206- 74 ; BHO, 595.
P. Peeters, "Observations sur Ia Vie syriaque de Mar Aba", dans RHPO, II, 116- 63.
BSO, I, 1- 4 (J .M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Catholicos Abā I was a widely venerated saint in the Church of the East. He was a reformer, theologian, confessor, Zoroastrian Convert, and student of the School of Nisibis. He wrote against
the practices of the Zoroastrians.
</note>
